<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Statistical_mechanics&action=edit&section=17.php.html" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Notes">Notes</span></h2>
<div class="reflist" style="list-style-type: decimal;">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-1"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The terms <i>statistical mechanics</i> and <i>statistical thermodynamics</i> are used interchangeably. <i><a href="Statistical_physics" title="Statistical physics">Statistical physics</a></i> is a broader term which includes statistical mechanics, but is sometimes also used as a synonym for statistical mechanics</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-10"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">see also the detailed explanation in <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://clesm.mae.ufl.edu/wiki.pub/index.php/Configuration_integral_(statistical_mechanics)">configuration integral</a></span></li>
</ol>
</div>
